comment: Muscala (ATL) makes marginal contact with Wall (WAS) that does not affect his SQBR.
Bazemore (ATL) makes contact to Porter Jr.'s (WAS) arm that affects his shot attempt.
Bazemore (ATL) makes marginal contact with Beal (WAS) off ball.
Howard (ATL) firms up his position and sets the screen on Wall (WAS).
Gortat (WAS) clamps the arm of Howard (ATL) and affects his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Howard (ATL) makes incidental contact with Gortat (WAS) that does not affect his FOM.
Howard (ATL) makes contact to Wall (WAS) that affects his SQBR.
Porter Jr. (WAS) makes marginal contact with Schroder (ATL) that does not affect his SQBR.
Porter Jr. (WAS) cleanly deflects the ball away from Schroder (ATL) on his drive to the basket.
The ball is last touched by Porter Jr. (WAS) prior to going OOB.
Beal (WAS) maintains legal guarding position on the drive to the basket by Schroder (ATL).
Oubre Jr. (WAS) makes marginal contact with Bazemore (ATL) that does not affect his SQBR.
Porter Jr. (WAS) makes contact to Bazemore's (ATL) arm that affects his SQBR.
Gortat (WAS) faces up with Muscala (ATL) and holds him, affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Muscala (ATL) and Wall (WAS) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Porter Jr. (WAS) makes incidental contact with Bazemore (ATL) that does not affect his SQBR.
Porter Jr. (WAS) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Bazemore (ATL) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Bradley (BOS) makes marginal contact with Butler (CHI) that does not affect his SQBR.
Butler (CHI) moves his pivot foot at the start of the dribble.
Horford (BOS) grabs and pulls down Lopez (CHI), affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Portis (CHI) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Thomas (BOS) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Portis (CHI) sets the screen on Crowder (BOS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Smart (BOS) makes incidental contact with Wade (CHI) that does not affect his SQBR.
[Observable in enhanced video] Grant (CHI) splits his feet prior to the start of his dribble.
Crowder (BOS) makes marginal contact with Butler (CHI) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Portis (CHI) makes marginal contact with Thomas (BOS) that does not affect his SQBR.
Butler (CHI) dislodges Smart (BOS) from his defensive position.
Horford (BOS) firms up his position and sets the screen on Portis (CHI). The contact following the screen is incidental.
Butler (CHI) legally contests Crowder's (BOS) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Thomas (BOS) commits a take foul on Butler (CHI).
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of CHI possession is overturned and BOS is awarded possession.
Horford (BOS) delivers the contact to Butler (CHI) on the screen and continues moving into him.
Lopez (CHI) makes marginal contact with Thomas (BOS) that does not affect his SQBR.
Butler (CHI) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Thomas (BOS) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Butler (CHI) and Smart (BOS) briefly engage and separate during the inbound.
Crowder (BOS) commits a take foul on Butler (CHI).
Crowder (BOS) inbounds the ball within 5 seconds.
Wade (CHI) makes marginal contact with Smart (BOS) during his follow-through.
